  "prompt": "What is the best MacBook for me?",
  "response": "Choosing the best MacBook depends on your specific needs, budget, and use case. Here\u2019s a breakdown to help you decide:\n\n---\n\n### **1. MacBook Air (M2)**\n- **Best For**: Everyday use, portability, students, casual creators.\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Lightweight and thin design.\n  - M2 chip for excellent performance and efficiency.\n  - Up to 18 hours of battery life.\n  - Retina display with high brightness and color accuracy.\n- **Why Choose It**: Ideal for general tasks like browsing, streaming, light photo/video editing, and office work. Great for those who prioritize portability.\n- **Price**: Starts at $1,099.\n\n---\n\n### **2. MacBook Air (M1)**\n- **Best For**: Budget-conscious users, students, and basic tasks.\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Affordable price point.\n  - M1 chip still delivers strong performance.\n  - Silent, fanless design.\n  - Up to 15 hours of battery life.\n- **Why Choose It**: A great value for basic tasks like web browsing, email, and light creative work.\n- **Price**: Starts at $999.\n\n---\n\n### **3. MacBook Pro 14-inch or 16-inch (M2 Pro/M2 Max)**\n- **Best For**: Professionals, power users, and creatives.\n- **Key Features**:\n  - M2 Pro or M2 Max chips for extreme performance.\n  - Larger, high-quality Mini-LED display with ProMotion (120Hz).\n  - Superior cooling system for sustained workloads.\n  - Up to 22 hours of battery life.\n  - Multiple ports (HDMI, SD card, Thunderbolt).\n- **Why Choose It**: Perfect for demanding tasks like video/photo editing, 3D rendering, software development, and heavy multitasking.\n- **Price**: Starts at $1,999 for 14-inch, $2,499 for 16-inch.\n\n---\n\n### **4. MacBook Pro 13-inch (M2)**\n- **Best For**: Users who want Pro features in a smaller form factor.\n- **Key Features**:\n  - M2 chip for solid performance.\n  - Touch Bar (though it\u2019s being phased out in newer models).\n  - Up to 20 hours of battery life.\n- **Why Choose It**: A good middle ground between the Air and the more powerful 14/16-inch Pro models.\n- **Price**: Starts at $1,299.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Considerations**\n- **Budget**: If you\u2019re on a tight budget, the M1 MacBook Air is still a fantastic choice.\n- **Portability**: The MacBook Air is the most portable, while the Pro models are heavier.\n- **Performance Needs**: For heavy workloads, the MacBook Pro 14-inch or 16-inch is the best option.\n- **Display**: If a larger or higher-quality display is important, go for the 14/16-inch Pro models.\n- **Future-Proofing**: If you want a laptop that will last for years, consider the M2 Air or Pro models.\n\nLet me know your specific needs or budget, and I can narrow it down further!",
